Rating: 3
I made these along with "Goat Cheese Quesadillas" and "Chicken and Mushroom Quesadillas" (both from epicurious) and they were all tasty. Great summer dinner or appetizer-I cooked them all on the grill, so the cooking step was part of the fun. Brush 1/2 of tortillas w/olive oil and put oil-side down on baking sheet. Top with whichever filling you're using, then cover with remaining tortillas. Brush top tortilla w/olive oil too. Grill over medium heat (3-4 min.?)or till lightly browned and filling is melty. Tip for turning them: use two large grilling spatulas and flip carefully. The melted cheese will help hold the filling in, but flip quickly to minimize spills.

